text.__SUMMARY__:
Hibbertia axillibarba is a shrub in the Dilleniaceae family that is native to Western Australia.The shrub has an erect habit and typically to a height of 0.7 m (2 ft 4 in). It blooms between September and October and produces yellow flowers.
The species has a limited distribution in a small area of the eastern Wheatbelt region of Western Australia around Kondinin where it is found on hills and ranges growing in lateritic soils.
